# React Query Standards

## Query Keys

Define as SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE constants in `config/queryKeys.ts` — never use inline strings.

```typescript
// config/queryKeys.ts
export const GET_FEATURE_KEY = 'get_feature_key';
```

✅ `queryKey: [GET_FEATURE_KEY, user?.uid]`
❌ `queryKey: ['feature', user.uid]`

`invalidateQueries({ queryKey: [GET_FEATURE_KEY] })` uses prefix matching — invalidates all queries whose key starts with that value, including `[GET_FEATURE_KEY, user.uid]`.

## Data Fetching Hook (`useFeatureData.ts`)

```typescript
export const useFeatureData = () => {
  const { user } = useAuth();

  return useQuery({
    queryKey: [GET_FEATURE_KEY, user?.uid],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const token = await user!.getIdToken();
      return featureService.getAll(token);
    },
    enabled: !!user,
  });
};
```

Usage: `const { data: items = [], isLoading } = useFeatureData();`

## Mutations Hook (`useFeatureMutations.ts`)

```typescript
export const useFeatureMutations = () => {
  const { user } = useAuth();
  const queryClient = useQueryClient();
  const invalidate = () =>
    queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: [GET_FEATURE_KEY] });

  const { mutate: createFeature, isPending: isCreating } = useMutation({
    mutationFn: async (data: FeatureInput) => {
      const token = await user!.getIdToken();
      return featureService.create(token, data);
    },
    onSuccess: () => {
      invalidate();
      // Web: toast.success('Created!') | Mobile: Alert.alert('Success', 'Created!')
    },
    onError: (error) => {
      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : 'Failed';
      // Web: toast.error(message) | Mobile: Alert.alert('Error', message)
    },
  });

  return { createFeature, isSubmitting: isCreating };
};
```

## Optimistic Delete (Recommended for Mobile)

Remove items instantly on delete — no full-screen loading state:

```typescript
onMutate: async (id) => {
  await queryClient.cancelQueries({ queryKey: [GET_FEATURE_KEY] });
  const previous = queryClient.getQueryData<Feature[]>([GET_FEATURE_KEY, user?.uid]);
  queryClient.setQueryData<Feature[]>([GET_FEATURE_KEY, user?.uid], old =>
    old ? old.filter(item => item.id !== id) : []
  );
  return { previous };
},
onError: (_err, _id, context) => {
  queryClient.setQueryData([GET_FEATURE_KEY, user?.uid], context?.previous);
},
onSettled: () => invalidate(),
```

No `onSuccess` alert for delete — the item disappearing is feedback enough.

## Key Rules

1. `enabled: !!user` — always guard queries that require auth
2. Always invalidate after mutations — never manually patch state
3. Destructure with fallback: `const { data: items = [] } = useFeatureData()`
4. Form state uses plain `useState` — never React Query
5. Never pass `refetch` to components — invalidation handles updates
6. No global `staleTime` — configure per-query when data changes rarely
